							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Moorgard posted this saturday night about the NDA being lifted:
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Participants in the Desert of Flames beta have been released from its Non-Disclosure Agreement (NDA) as of today.
<br />
 
<br />
We wanted to announce this in public so there aren't any doubts as to whether some of the posts you'll be seeing from testers are okay to read or not. 
<br />
 
<br />
The beta boards will continue to require beta tester access both to view and post in.  This isn't to keep information secret, but for two reasons: 
<br />
 
<br />
1) People posted messages there on the assumption that it was a private forum.  We don't want to change that midstream.
<br />
2) To keep the same feeling of a smaller community of people all testing on the same server.
<br />
 
<br />
Feel free to discuss DoF details in all appropriate public boards and channels.
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.TheScoutsSanctuary.com" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://www.TheScoutsSanctuary.com/images/Khalysig.jpg" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
