							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Speed enhancements in EQ1 were somewhat larger than in EQ2.  Song of Travel in EQ1 had the invisibility and see invis components like this one (except in EQ1, invis seldom worked on any undead or many casting mobs).  The EQ1 version also had levitation, an ability completely missing from EQ2 (unless you count carpets and griffons).  If an EQ1 bard equipped a high-end drum, he could get his speed up to 2.5 times normal run speed, which was the absolute game speed limit.<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://www.mausturm.com/EQ2/images/dingsig1.jpg"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
